							<h2><span style="color:#006FC9;">GET THE FULL STORY FROM EXITING EMPLOYEES</span></h2>
							<br>
							<p>Most managers believe employees leave because of 'pull' factors such as better pay or career opportunities, rather than 'push' factors that occur long before employees look for greener pastures. Many exit programs don't focus on what happened when the employee first set their mind on leaving. Workforce Retention specialises in getting meaningful information through the exit process, and reports this back to business leaders so action can be taken.</p>
<br>
						</div>
